i found to be too sour. watch the amount of lime juice, put in 2 tablespoons and taste before adding the rest . if i made it again i would puree all of the bell peppers, and chiles instead of only half.

Rating: 4
Everyone loved this! I used 2 whole jalapenos, 2 garlic cloves, 4 tbsp lime juice, and about 1/3 cup cilantro. I also subbed whole-milk yogurt for the sour cream. The soup didn't taste too great when I first tried it, but after 2 hours in the fridge it was fabulous!

Rating: 3
To chill, I placed a covered bowl in the freezer's ice tray for 10 minutes. This worked much better than the ice and water bath.

