Rating: 3
I didn't think this was bland at all! In fact, my tastebuds are still burning from the jalapeno! My only alterations were cutting back on the cilantro by about half (I'm not a huge fan of it), using only 1 jalapeno and 1 yellow pepper, using a box of firm silken tofu in place of the sour cream, and white pepper in place of the black (I'm allergic). It got rave reviews. I will definitely be making this again.

Rating: 3
In the future, I'd substitute plain yogurt for sour cream. I added white pepper, chives, and scallions to spice up. I'm a big cucumber soup fan and this was easier than my usual chicken-broth based recipe.

Rating: 3
I made this according to the recipe with the exception of adding 2 small jalapenos. I thought it was just right and not too hot or spicy. It tastes even better the next day. It was great for a hot summer night. Enjoy!

